#### Bio 

I work at the intersection of biological psychiatry, computational biology, and biostatistics, leveraging large human datasets to better understand how genomic signatures associate with brain development and subsequent dysregulation in brain disorders. 

#### Positions

- Associate Professor, Johns Hopkins University (Departments of Mental Health, Biostatistics, Psychiatry & Behavioral Sciences, Neuroscience, and Human Genetics) [on leave]

- Lead Investigator, Lieber Institute for Brain Development [2012-2020]

#### Lab Alumni

- PhD Students: Kira A. Perzel Mandell, Matthew Nguyen Tran, Brianna K. Barry, Amanda J. Price, Leonardo Collado-Torres
- Postbac Fellows: Stephen A. Semick, BaDoi N. Phan, Nikolay A. Ivanov
- Staff: Leonardo Collado-Torres, Arta Seyedian, Joshua Stolz, Louise Huuki, Madhavi Tippani, Nicholas Eagles, Emily E. Burke

